g.text: Stage 3 - Pair the Smart Key:
1. Navigate to Chassis Diagnostics.
2. Press the motorcycle's Power button (Note: the motorcycle will not appear to power ON).
3. Within 10 seconds, click Immobiliser Diagnostics.
4. Pair the smart key using the Add New Key function.
5. Press the button on the smart key after it has been successfully paired.
Stage 6 - Pair the Engine ECM with the Immobiliser:
1. Switch the engine start/stop switch to the RUN position.
2. Navigate to Immobiliser Diagnostics and pair the engine ECM and immobiliser.
Stage 8 - Final Steps:
1. Turn the ignition off for at least 60 seconds.
2. Check the ignition can be turned ON and engine started using each key.
3. Check all ECMs for stored DTCs and erase as necessary.
4. If fitted, set up the tyre pressure monitoring system as described in the Triumph Diagnostic Tool User Guide.
Stage 4 - Pair the Electronic Steering Lock (if fitted).
Stage 1 - Preliminary steps:
1. Install the replacement keyless ECM.
2. Reconnect the battery.
3. Make sure you have all the new keys ready.
4. Connect the diagnostic tool.
Stage 2 - Partial Keyless ECM download:
1. Select the correct Keyless ECM calibration for download using Manual Model Selection.
2. Do not click Confirm to start the download at this point.
3. Press the motorcycle's Power On/Off button (Note: the motorcycle will not appear to power ON).
4. Within 10 seconds, click Confirm to start the download.
5. Follow the on screen instructions at the start of the download.
6. Click Cancel when the download reaches 100% and you are prompted turn the ignition ON.
Stage 5 - Full Keyless ECM download:
1. Make sure the smart key is in range and turn the ignition ON. The instruments and headlight should now turn ON.
2. Complete a full keyless ECM download using the normal download method.
3. Follow all on-screen instructions during the download.
4. Click Finish when the download has completed.
Stage 7 - Pair the Passive Keys:
1. Pair the two passive keys using the Add New Key function.
